**License:** GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE v3 or higher.

This library solves the constrained Hartree-Fock-Bogoliubov equations using a cylindrical one- or two-center basis.  

Some example runs and a Jupyter example notebook can be found in `examples/`.

See the main page of the HFB3 project here: `https://www.github.com/cea-phynu/hfb3`.
